<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-19343] Predicates are shared between templated routes in Java DSL with simple predicate builder</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-19343</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Templated routes with the &quot;choice&quot; processor share the same Predicate (&lt;em&gt;org.apache.camel.model.WhenDefinition#expression#predicate&lt;/em&gt;) and because it is initialized with template parameters of the first route created, it fails for the other routes. This is particularly visible when using Kamelets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proposed solution would be for &lt;em&gt;org.apache.camel.model.WhenDefinition&lt;/em&gt; to accept Supplier&amp;lt;Predicate&amp;gt; (or similar) instead of the Predicate instance but that would require static factory methods in &lt;em&gt;org.apache.camel.support.builder.PredicateBuilder&lt;/em&gt; to be refactored or a new class to be created.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/bartoszpop/CAMEL-19343/blob/main/src/test/java/io/github/bartoszpop/camel/Camel19343Test.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;This&lt;/a&gt; is a unit test. It fails for the second instance of the template.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
