                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17743516" author="davsclaus" created="Sun, 16 Jul 2023 11:50:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is because you use the fluent builder on simple. If you do this&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;                .when(simple(&quot;&apos;&lt;tt&gt;&quot; + CHOICE_PARAMETER + &quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&apos; == &apos;some&apos;&quot;) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then it works fine and this is also the way other DSLs and Kamelets are doing this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17743525" author="bartoszpop" created="Sun, 16 Jul 2023 12:51:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems to work. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17743623" author="davsclaus" created="Mon, 17 Jul 2023 05:13:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a section to the docs about this limitation with simple fluent builder style.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
